net.java.jddac.jmdi.comm.xml
Interface ArgTypeConverter

All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultArgTypeConverter, DefaultArgTypeConverterJ2me, DefaultArgTypeConverterJ2se
public interface ArgTypeConverter

A handler that transforms JDDAC XML to/from Java binary objects. Classes that implement this interface are used by the ArgXmlCoder class to convert Java objects to/from the JDDAC Arg XML format.
To implement ArgXmlCoder support for a new type, create a new class that implements this interface, implement the methods for the new type, and in the your CoderInterface class, register an instance of the new class with the ArgXmlCoder.addObjectHandlers method.
This interface supports 2 different types, a Scalar type and a Complex type. The isComplexType method is used to differentiate them.
A scalar type is for a class with a value that can be represented by a single string in the JDDAC Arg Xml. An example is a date object that might be represented by the tag <arg t="date">10/23/2006</arg>.
A Complex type are for classes where the value can not be represented by a single scalar value. There are 2 versions of Complex types. The first is a set of values that are best represented by a Map of name/value pairs, this is the ArgArray version. The second is a set of values that can be represented as an ordered list of values, this is the Vector version. The isVectorComplexType method is used to differentiate them.
For the ArgArray version of a Complex type, the conversion routines convert the Java object to an ArgArray of name/value pairs. The name can be any String, and the value can be any supported type, scalar or complex. An example is a simple location object that might be converted into the following XML: 

   <argArray>
     <arg n="lat" t="float">123.1</arg>
     <arg n="lon" t="float">45.3</arg>
   </argArray>
For the Vector version of a Complex type, the conversion routines convert the Java object to a Vector of values. The values can be any supported type, scalar or complex. An example is date array object that might be converted into the following XML: 
   <argArray t="dateArray" l="2">
     <arg n="0" t="date">10/23/2006</arg>
     <arg n="1" t="date">1/2/2003</arg>
   </argArray>
